headline: Palantir Earnings Are Never Boring. Expectations, and the Stock Price, Are High.
summary: Investors should brace themselves for  Palantir  Technologies’ third-quarter earnings report, due Monday afternoon.  Demand for Palantir software—it offers a platform that integrates an organization’s data, from disparate sources and in various formats, into simple dashboards that use artificial intelligence to aid in decision-making—is taking off.  Wall Street analysts expect sales of $1.09 billion, up 50% since last year, and adjusted earnings-per-share growth of 68%.
